# TypeScript + Next.js standards

## Code quality
- Keep strict typing; avoid `any` unless documented and justified.
- Prefer small pure helpers for complex logic.
- Keep components focused and avoid hidden side effects.

## Data and async safety
- Handle async failures explicitly with user-safe fallbacks.
- Validate external input at boundaries.
- Avoid leaking sensitive data to client logs or errors.

## Testing and verification
- For bug fixes, add or update tests when feasible.
- For behavior changes, include manual verification steps in PR.
- Run lint/tests for touched scope before finalizing.
